<font color="#FF0000">SUFFERING SOCIAL ILL'S</font><br>
<tt>Fri Jan  9 19:03:10 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
Captain, My Captain<br>
We pass laws and legislation to compel individuals to do what their conscience has failed to stop them from doing (the symptoms). We fail to realize that we can't pass laws that will heal a wicked heart (the real problem).<br><br>
What can we do? We argue about abortions, and the right to life but fail to spent time with our children, teenagers, fail to teach them what is good, and what is right in God's eyes because we have never taken the time to examine what God desires and wants from us as individuals. Seeking the common goal seems to be where everyone is now heading. Let's all agree or let's all do what we preceive is good or bed in our own eyes. <br>
The scriptures tell us that the beginning of knowledge is the Fear of God, actually in Hebrew, it means the respect of God. We respect those whom we give credit for accomplishments, for moral integrity and who we see as above us in a respective field. Respecting God for His goodness begins to humble us for our failures, acknowledging our own wrongs begins the journey toward salvation, and acceptance and willing to serve God above our own desires. Willling to serve others above my own. Marriage is not a 50/50 venture, social do gooders tell us it is. It should always be each partner giving 90% or more, not expecting any return.<br><br>
But, Individuals ignore what they know inside is wrong, often no one needs to tell us, our own hearts tells us so.<br>
When we ignore those inner truths the mind makes adjustments to a new theory, a new acceptance, but still within, our hearts know it's wrong. Ignoring the truth only makes our hearts grow darker. Soon even the Spirit of God leaves the individual, and he/she is given over to a depraved mind and when that happens such an individual seeks out, other like minded individuals that are willing to participate in their sin and thus obtain a social acceptance in a level they will identify with and accept, but still they remain troubled and full of woe. Homosexuals are not GAY, but miserable and suffering, but they blame society for their social rejection. <br><br>
Fears of an economic collapse surfaced yesterday, when the promise of a $43-billion bailout from the International Monetary Fund, did not change Indonesia's form of government. They simply do not want to invest their own funds in that nation's most urgent needs, so now it has produced an economy woe. Do we have a right to interveen there, or let them eat crow? <br><br>
Kennedy blamed the Joint Chief of Staff for their failure to warn him against the Bay of Pigs invasion, but he never consulted them before deciding to do what he and his close hand chosen government officers that were all like minded decided to do. The same thing happened in the pre-Vietnam Laos conflict and because of that other measures (Vietnam conflict) surfaced. <br><br>
In a multitude of counsel there is much wisdom but when we don't use those resources or have already made up our stubborn minds we and our children and, perhaps a generation of children eventually suffer for the wrongs we did or will do today.<br><br>
Payday is not always on Tuesday, I never once saw, Wimpy in the old Popeye comic stripe and Saturday morning shows ever pay for his hamburgers; it was always &quot;if you give me a hamburger today, I will gladly pay you Tuesday.&quot; But he never paid for them, we all knew he wasn’t going to pay, but thought it funny.<br>
 <br>
Songs, our environment, social structures friends, relatives all influence our everyday practices.<br>
Good dwells in all of us as does evil, we have the choices to make everyday, sin is enjoyable otherwise we wouldn't pursuit it so hard. <br>
The problem is made only greater when a sin is justified for whatever reason, or accepted as a consequence of the times in which we live. When we blame others for our failures.<br><br>
Prostitution is now called a social disorder in Vietnam, (can't wait for the democrats to identify it as such and pass legislation to prevent cruelty to women suffering from such a social disorder). But no matter what we call it, it is still sin. The above remark about democrats is an example, I shouldn't have said it, but I did. Left it in instead of editing it out. Does leaving it in serve now as a purpose? Justifying its insertion? Justifying a sin, I knew that its not right to say, but said it anyways then tried to justify it by saying it proves my point. The trouble is, that's its wrong, its still sin. <br><br>
War and prostitution are two of the worlds oldest professionals and they will always be with us. Payday does not always come on Tuesday, it never did for Wimpy, but judgement from above will come. <br>
Right now its raining outside, I love the rain if I walk outside I will get wet. It rains on the good and on the bad. Rain is no respecter of persons, God is no respecter of persons, and I just know that the more I restrain from doing wrong the happier I am. The less sins I commit the happier my home life is; now I need to teach that to my children and they to their children. I can't wait for our government to pass legislation in order to obey what I know I should do. I can’t wait for Legislators to adopt a program against every sin. <br><br>
I need to do what is right now, today, at home. No government involvement needed and when it rains and we get wet, we dry off and go on, no use in seeking revenge, God knows His own, knows our hearts and daily lives, its Him I must please. I must examine my own heart daily to see why I do what I do, the good and the evil. Have to choose life or death. We all make those choices daily, there is more good then evil in the world and that is good, let us contribute to that.<br><br>
Well, Ed you got me thinking and I guess I just rambled on, but those are my thoughts. Its not the little RED book we should be reading, that won't change our lives, its the large black covered one on the coffe table, of course we'll have to brush away the cobwebs first. 
